window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>It is night in the South Seas near Tahiti, and the ship HMS <i>Bounty</i> has begun the long voyage home to England. But the sailors on the ship are angry men, and they have swords and guns. They pull the captain out of bed and take him up on deck. He tries to run, but a sailor holds a knife to his neck. \"Do that again, Captain Bligh, and youâ€™re a dead man!\" he says. </p> <p>The mutiny on the <i>Bounty</i> happened in April 1789. This is the true story of Captain Bligh and Fletcher Christian, and the ship that never came home to England. </p> <p>An Oxford Bookworms Library reader for learners of English.</p>"; 
